WordPress Twenty Twenty theme to Gatsby using the new gatsby-source-wordpress@v4.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-03-07T15:19:32.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Free Tutorials / Courses</h2><h3>Video Tutorials</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>2019.11: <a href=\"https://whatjackhasmade.co.uk/series/gatsby-wordpress-2019/\">25+ Videos - Gatsby + WordPress (2019) Complete Course</a> - The series focuses on how we can use WordPress as a headless CMS with a GraphQL schema to interface with. After setting up our WordPress site and theme, we'll move onto Gatsby and how we can use our new schema to generate content for our Gatsby site, programmatically generating pages, converting Gutenberg blocks to React components and finishing off the chapter with a focus on SEO in Gatsby.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-03-07T15:06:24.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Articles and Talks</h2>","itemHTML":"<li>2021.02: <a href=\"https://www.gatsbyjs.com/blog/wordpress-integration\">Announcing Gatsby’s New WordPress Integration</a></li>","updatedAt":"2021-03-07T15:03:04.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Articles and Talks</h2>","itemHTML":"<li>2021.02: <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Me_A0HBYXx8\">Jason Bahl of WPGraphQL's role in the operating system for the web</a></li>","updatedAt":"2021-03-07T15:03:04.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Articles and Talks</h2>","itemHTML":"<li>2021.02: <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8SAdtU8HAwM\">Torque News Drop: Jason Bahl and WPGraphQL</a></li>","updatedAt":"2021-03-07T15:03:04.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Articles and Talks</h2>","itemHTML":"<li>2021.02: <a href=\"https://wptavern.com/gatsby-launches-new-wordpress-integration-expanding-support-for-headless-architecture\">Gatsby Launches New WordPress Integration, Expanding Support for Headless Architecture</a></li>","updatedAt":"2021-03-07T15:03:04.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Articles and Talks</h2>","itemHTML":"<li>2020.11: <a href=\"https://www.wpgraphql.com/2020/11/16/announcing-wpgraphql-v1/\">Announcing WPGraphQL v1.0</a></li>","updatedAt":"2021-03-07T15:03:04.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Articles and Talks</h2>","itemHTML":"<li>2020.07: <a href=\"https://css-tricks.com/my-long-journey-to-a-decoupled-wordpress-gatsby-site/\">My Long Journey to a Decoupled WordPress Gatsby Site</a></li>","updatedAt":"2021-03-07T15:03:04.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Plugins</h2><h4>Essential Plugins</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/wp-gatsby/\">WPGatsby</a> - This plugin configures your WordPress site to be an optimized source for Gatsby.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-03-07T15:03:04.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Plugins</h2><h4>WPGraphQL Extensions</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/funkhaus/wp-graphql-cors\">WPGraphQL Cors</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/funkhaus/wp-graphql-cors\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">37</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":37,\"repo\":\"funkhaus/wp-graphql-cors\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - This FREE plugin from @kidunot89 and @byfunkhaus claims to enable authentication with WPGraphQL to “just work” by allowing you to set CORS headers that GraphQL will accept, which means WordPress default auth cookies can be accepted.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-03-07T15:03:04.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Plugins</h2><h4>WPGraphQL Extensions</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/builtbycactus/total-counts-for-wp-graphql\">Total Counts for WPGraphQL</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/builtbycactus/total-counts-for-wp-graphql\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">5</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":5,\"repo\":\"builtbycactus/total-counts-for-wp-graphql\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - This FREE plugin from @builtbycactus exposes total counts to connections in the WPGraphQL Schema.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-03-07T15:03:04.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Plugins</h2><h4>WPGraphQL Extensions</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/roborourke/wp-graphql-meta\">WPGraphQL Meta</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/roborourke/wp-graphql-meta\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">16</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":16,\"repo\":\"roborourke/wp-graphql-meta\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - This FREE plugin from @robertorourke exposes meta registered via the WordPress register_meta API to WPGraphQL.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-03-07T15:03:04.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Plugins</h2><h4>WPGraphQL Extensions</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/wp-graphql/wp-graphql-meta-query\">WPGraphQL Meta Query</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/wp-graphql/wp-graphql-meta-query\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">29</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":29,\"repo\":\"wp-graphql/wp-graphql-meta-query\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Adds Meta_Query support to the WPGraphQL Plugin for postObject query args.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-03-07T15:03:04.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Plugins</h2><h4>WPGraphQL Extensions</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/Quartz/wp-graphql-persisted-queries\">WPGraphQL Persisted Queries</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/Quartz/wp-graphql-persisted-queries\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">15</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":15,\"repo\":\"Quartz/wp-graphql-persisted-queries\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - This FREE plugin from @qz adds the ability to use Persisted Queries with WPGraphQL.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-03-07T15:03:04.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Plugins</h2><h4>WPGraphQL Extensions</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/darylldoyle/wp-graphql-offset-pagination\">WPGraphQL Offset Pagination</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/darylldoyle/wp-graphql-offset-pagination\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">9</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":9,\"repo\":\"darylldoyle/wp-graphql-offset-pagination\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - This FREE plugin from @enshrined adds basic offset pagination as opposed to the standard Cursor based pagination that ships with WPGraphQL.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-03-07T15:03:04.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Plugins</h2><h4>WPGraphQL Extensions</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/ashhitch/wp-graphql-send-mail\">WPGraphQL Send Email</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/ashhitch/wp-graphql-send-mail\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">9</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":9,\"repo\":\"ashhitch/wp-graphql-send-mail\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - This FREE plugin from @Ash_Hitchcock allows you to send emails via a simple mutation. Includes the abilitty to restrict sending to trusted origins.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-03-07T15:03:04.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Plugins</h2><h4>Other helpful Plugins</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/headless-mode/\">Headless Mode</a> - Headless mode sets up a redirect for all users trying to access the site. The only requests that are granted admission are ones that are either trying to access the REST API, the WP GraphQL API, or any logged-in user looking to access the headless install to edit or create posts.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-03-07T15:03:04.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Plugins</h2><h4>Other helpful Plugins</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/crgeary/wp-jamstack-deployments\">WP JAMstack Deployments</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/crgeary/wp-jamstack-deployments\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">228</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":228,\"repo\":\"crgeary/wp-jamstack-deployments\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - WordPress plugin for JAMstack deployments on Netlify (and other platforms).</li>","updatedAt":"2021-03-07T15:03:04.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Free Tutorials / Courses</h2><h3>Written Tutorials</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>2018.08: <a href=\"https://justinwhall.com/headless-wordpress-gatsby-netlify-continous-deployment/\">Headless WordPress + Gatsby + Netlify continuous deployment</a> - Guide showing how to create a WordPress + Gatsby + Netlify setup in a few simple steps.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-03-07T15:03:04.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Starters</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/zeevo/gatsby-starter-wordpress-blog\">Gatsby Starter Blog</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/zeevo/gatsby-starter-wordpress-blog\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">5</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":5,\"repo\":\"zeevo/gatsby-starter-wordpress-blog\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Blog starter with enough features to be production ready out of the box.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-03-07T15:03:04.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Starters</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/henrikwirth/gatsby-starter-wordpress-advanced\">Gatsby WordPress Starter Advanced</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/henrikwirth/gatsby-starter-wordpress-advanced\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">59</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":59,\"repo\":\"henrikwirth/gatsby-starter-wordpress-advanced\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - An advanced Gatsby + WordPress starter, that is built along a tutorial series and works with ACF flexible content fields to create content blocks/layouts.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-12-27T22:26:20.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Plugins</h2><h4>Other helpful Plugins</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/advanced-custom-fields/\">Advanced Custom Fields</a> - <a href=\"https://www.advancedcustomfields.com/pro/\">ACF PRO</a></li>","updatedAt":"2019-12-14T12:45:47.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Plugins</h2><h4>Other helpful Plugins</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/polylang/\">Polylang</a></li>","updatedAt":"2019-12-14T12:45:47.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Free Tutorials / Courses</h2><h3>Written Tutorials</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>2019.11: <a href=\"https://dev.to/nevernull/overview-guide-to-gatsby-wordpress-starter-advanced-with-previews-i18n-and-more-583l\">Guide to Gatsby WordPress Starter Advanced with Previews, i18n and more</a> - A tutorial series starting with the basic setup of WordPress and Gatsby with WPGraphQL and then dives into more advanced subjects like deployments, previews, i18n and a page-builder like setup with ACF flexible cotent fields.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-11-27T10:01:21.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Free Tutorials / Courses</h2><h3>Video Tutorials</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>2019.07: <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9KGuI0UmpMw\">Crash Course: Headless WordPress with WPGraphQL, ACF, and React</a> - In this video, Alex Young (WPCasts) goes over how to get a simple headless WordPress setup with WPGraphQL and React.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-11-27T01:50:03.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Plugins</h2><h4>Essential Plugins</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/wp-graphql/wp-graphql\">WPGraphQL</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/wp-graphql/wp-graphql\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;f